        <!-- About Section-->
        <section class="page-section bg-primary text-white mb-0" id="about">
            <div class="container">
            <!-- About Section Heading-->
            <h2 class="page-section-heading text-center text-uppercase text-white">About</h2>
            <div class="divider-custom divider-light">
            <div class="divider-custom divider-light">
                <!-- About Section Content-->
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-lg-4 ml-auto">
                        <p class="lead">Seniors Monday Winter League Rules 2020/21
                            <br></br>
                            Two Stableford league competitions will be run over winter each of 10 weeks duration. The first from 2nd November and the second from Monday 11 January. Play will be from the yellow tees on the Lakes course each Monday to allow all members to take part (Buggies NOT being allowed on the Dawson). Players must register with the organising committee before playing in the league by signing the entry form on the Notice Board. It is not compulsory to enter both the usual Monday sweep and the league together.
                            <br></br>
                            Entry Fee and Prizes:
                            The entry fee will be £1 per round beyond the existing £2 entry fee for competitions on Mondays. Prizes for Monday competitions will be paid out as normal. The £1 league entry will be accumulated over the 10 weeks and be paid out as far down the league as reasonable depending on the size of the pot
                            <br></br>
                            Eligibility:
                            Players must be members of the Senior Section and have a competition handicap
                            <br></br>
                            Scoring<br></br>
                            The following scoring system will be adopted: Winner - 18 points, Runner Up – 15, 3rd place – 12 4th -10, 5th - 9 6th 8 etc down to 14th – 2, then 15th and all subsequent places 1.
                            <br></br>
                            Notification of Results
                            <br></br>
                            Results and handicap changes will be posted on the notice board on Monday and the league table will be updated on Wednesday. The results will also be emailed to members. (On your Scorecard please fill in the date and your name clearly. Players who do not return a scorecard for their round will not be awarded a league point)
                            <br></br>
                            Entry Procedures<br></br>
                            Pay your £1 entry fee to the competition administrator on the day and ensure that it has been recorded by him
                            <br></br>
                            Course Conditions<br></br>
                            Players must accept that the weather and consequently conditions on the course may vary from week to week. Also course set up may differ ie use of winter greens etc. with different tee and flag positions. Results for the week are accepted irrespective of course conditions. Mats may be used.
                            <br></br>
                            Handicap adjustments<br></br>
                            All handicap adjustments are temporary and apply to all Senior winter competitions including Fridays. Your handicap will revert to its pre-competition status when the 2021 season starts next April. Handicaps will be adjusted using the same principles as for summer play.
                            <br></br>
                            Exceptional play<br></br>
                            Where the organisers feel that a player has returned a number of scores better than his current competition handicap a further reduction may be made. Account will be taken of the course set up, weather conditions prevailing at the time of play and fellow competitor’s scores.
                            The organisers committee will endeavour to have all adjustments to handicaps finalised by the Monday morning.<br></br>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-4 ml-auto">
                        <p class="lead">Longhirst seniors meet every Monday in the Club House. Pre-booked tee times are normally allocated as There are 2 annual competitions, the Spring Cup and the Autumn Cup which are held away at different venues in the local area.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
